    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look for a high-ceiling performance today, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (83.19) and **Andy Pages** (71.16). Both are positioned to capitalize on a favorable matchup against Michael Lorenzen, benefiting from a 14% park-factor surge that elevates their expected output well above their baseline projections. **Jacob Wilson** (74.08) also emerges as a high-value play; despite his modest base, he draws a prime matchup against Noah Schultz (6.23 xERA) and receives a 19% boost in efficiency due to the soft opposing pitching, making him an essential start. **Miguel Vargas** (66.33) remains a high-floor selection, with his value bolstered by a rare combination of park favorability and the 86% stolen base success rate against the opposing battery, providing a subtle but crucial edge in our scarcest category.\n\nWe have opted to bench **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (54.98), who narrowly missed the cut for the final utility spot. While his projected order position and favorable platoon dynamics against Robbie Ray kept him in the conversation, the optimizer favored **Nolan Schanuel** (55.84) due to a higher raw base projection that barely edged out **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**\u2019s situational advantages. Management remains cautious regarding **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.26); while his talent demands a start, he carries a 34% rain risk that could lead to a shortened game or postponement, capping his total utility today. All other lineup slots are confirmed pending official orders, though the current projections assume standard placements that prioritize **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker** at the top of the lineup to maximize run-scoring opportunities.",
